# .cursorrules — Cursor-specific overrides
# Universal rules are in AGENTS.md. Read it first, always.

## Workflow
Before starting ANY task:
1. Read AGENTS.md for architecture and global rules
2. Identify the task domain and read the matching skill in `.agents/skills/`
3. State which skill you loaded before writing code

## Cursor-specific
- Use Composer for multi-file tasks
- When editing a file, always check if a related test file exists and update it
- Diffs must be reviewed by the developer before applying to migrations or SQL files